hool drop-offs\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"school\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1071}, {\"ngram\": \"training camps\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"World Cup competitions\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been quick to praise the adaptability of her crew mates Esme Both, Samantha Redgrave and Rebecca Shorten in fitting around her life demands, so too her coach James Harris.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samantha_Mulder\", \"score\": 0.9874614089434346, \"rank\": 0.012697803153862399, \"text\": \"Samantha\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samantha_Mulder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samantha_Mulder\"}, {\"begin\": 1222, \"end\": 1237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Shorten\", \"score\": 0.9999947512179875, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebecca Shorten\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Shorten\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Shorten\"}, {\"begin\": 1291, \"end\": 1303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Jam_and_Terry_Lewis\", \"score\": 0.9999315066413231, \"rank\": 6.849805047845556e-05, \"text\": \"James Harris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Jam_and_Terry_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Jam_and_Terry_Lewis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the adaptability\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1170}, {\"ngram\": \"her crew mates\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"Esme Both\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"fitting\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1248}, {\"ngram\": \"her life\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And in the women's four they had comfortably been the No1 crew in the world this year winning World Cups as well as the European Championships.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1449, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the No1 crew\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1368}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"World Cups\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1410}, {\"ngram\": \"the European Championships\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her Olympics have all been contrasting experiences.\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her Olympics\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"contrasting experiences\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At London 2012, she and rowing partner Heather Stanning, who was also here watching as aTeam GBathlete ambassador, had not been household names before winning Team GB's first gold of a home Games.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998082926325, \"rank\": 1.9169890735327842e-07, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1542, \"end\": 1558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_Stanning\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heather Stanning\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_Stanning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_Stanning\"}, {\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.866686496306219e-15, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"aTeam GBathlete ambassador\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1616}, {\"ngram\": \"household names\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1646}, {\"ngram\": \"a home Games\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1698}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four years on, they were as much a favourite for gold as was humanly possible, And in Tokyo last time around Glover had said it was simply a victory to make it on to the plane having left behind one-year-old twins at home.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.6933659394367723, \"rank\": 0.4422383649894232, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.999995920542141, \"rank\": 4.079472155804395e-06, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"as much a favourite\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1745}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"a victory\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"the plane\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1876}, {\"ngram\": \"one-year-old twins\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 1922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today wo;; likely be the denouement to Glover's illustrious career at the age of 38.\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.999995920542141, \"rank\": 4.079472155804395e-06, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the denouement\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2002}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But having twice quit but returned, never say never That Games had only been possible when Covid caused a year's delay to proceedings and she trained at home in between the twins' naps to see whether a comeback might be possible.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Games\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"Covid\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"a year's delay\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"proceedings\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2167}, {\"ngram\": \"the twins' naps\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2194}, {\"ngram\": \"a comeback\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said she was as proud of her Tokyo appearance as the preceding two golds.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2276, \"end\": 2281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.6933659394367723, \"rank\": 0.4422383649894232, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the preceding two golds\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here in Paris at her fourth Games she was back at being the favourites but the Dutch four got off to a quick start and, despite immense pressure from their British rivals, held on.\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2330, \"end\": 2335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.211679478081902e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2478, \"end\": 2485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_Kingdo